        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The dominance of ionic species in precipitation was geographically differs from locations and regions are presented in Table 8. In Alibagh [Cl > Na > Mg > Ca > SO4 > NO3 > NH4 > K], Goa [Cl > Na > Ca > Mg > SO4 > NO3 > K], and Bombay [Cl > Na > Ca > Mg > SO4 > NO3 > K] showed dominance of Cl (Naik et al. 2002; Parashar et al. 2001; Segeuira 1976) whereas at Colaba [Na > Cl > Ca > Mg > SO4 > NO3 > NH4 > K], Silent Valley [Na > Ca > Cl > NO3 > SO4 > Mg > K>NH4], Chembur [Na > Cl > Ca > NO, > NH4 > Mg > SO4 > K], there is a dominance of Na as these sites are nearer to sea coast (Naik et al. 2002; Rao et al. 1995; Khemani et al. 1994).",
